<doc id="952312" wikidata="Q5521254" url="?curid=952312" title="Gangster World">
<text>Gangster World (alternatively titled The Outsider for its video release) is a 1997 made-for-TV science fiction film directed by David Bishop and written by Patrick Highsmith and Evan Spiliotopoulos. It was about a futuristic theme park in which people interact with androids in violent (and sometimes sexual) gangster-style scenarios. Despite the title and premise, it is unconnected with the film &quot;Westworld&quot;.

In 1998, a DVD was released of the film.

